If you just instantiate a bean which implements SeedListener in your 
crawl configuration (Spring XML/&#39;cxml&#39;), Spring autowiring will ensure 
it&#39;s included among any other SeedListeners in that set.

Understanding everything at this bit of Spring documentation will be a 
great help in making advanced changes to Heritrix3 configuration:

http://static.springsource.org/spring/docs/2.5.x/reference/beans.html

See especially the section on @Autowired, and how a typed-collection can 
be autowired to include all instances of that type:

http://static.springsource.org/spring/docs/2.5.x/reference/beans.html#beans-autowired-annotation

- Gordon @ IA

